<%= render :partial => "header", :locals => { :method_name => "Random Ballot", :winners => results[:winners], :warnings => results[:warnings] } %>
<div>
	<h4>Description</h4>
	<p>In random ballots, each voter expresses a preference for a single candidate. The winner is selected at random from single voter's ballot.</p>

	<%= render :partial => "preferences_warning", :locals => { :method_name => "Random Ballot", :warnings => results[:warnings] } %>
	
	<h4>Tally</h4>
	<table class="ui-state-highlight ui-corner-all">
		<thead>
			<tr><th>Candidate</th><th>Votes</th<th>Supporting demographics</th></tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			<% results[:supporters].keys.each do |c| %>
				<tr><td><%= c %></td><td><%= results[:votes][c] %></td><td><%= results[:supporters][c].join(', ') %></td></tr>
			<% end %>
		</tbody>
	</table>
	<p>All we do now is randomly pick one of these ballots.</p>

	<%= render :partial => "result", :locals => { :winners => results[:winners] } %>
</div>
